			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="yi">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540377_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>גבית-עדות</p>
					<p>איבערגעגעבן דורך <persName ref="#ehri_et_strazshi_yoffe_sonya">סוניא יפה</persName> געב. אין <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">ווילנע</placeName> 17.IX.1946</p>
					<p>אויפ. <persName ref="#ehri_et_levental_nachman">לעווענטאל נחמן</persName>.</p>
					<p><placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">קאיליס</placeName> איז געווען אַ זא <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">לאגער</term> 2 בלאקן, אויף די <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">רידז-שמיגלעגא</placeName>-גאס, ווו
						ס'האבן געוווינט און <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">געארבייט</term> די יידן-קירזשנער. געפונען האבן זיך דארטן אַ 2000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">מאן</term>. וואס האבן
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">געארבייט</term> ביי פוטער-קורזשנעריי. די גאנצע צייט איז געווען <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">פערהעלטניסמעסיג גוט</term> . די לעצטע צייט
						אין יוני 1944 יאר האט מען גענומען 50 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">מאן</term> שטארקע <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">מענער</term> אויף <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">פאנארי</placeName> צו <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">ארבייט</term> און מער זייניען זיי ניט צוריקגעקומען. אין 27/III-1944 האט מען צוזאמענגענומען די <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">קינדער</term>, יונגע און אלטע <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">לייט</term>, מ'האט זיי <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">אנגעטון</term> זויבער און געפירט אין <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">שפיטאל</term>, כלומרשט אויף אַ בעזוך – מ'האט זיי דורך איין טור אריינגעפירט
						און נאך דער צווייטער טור ארויסגעפירט. דארט זיינען שוין געשטאנען די <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">אוקראאינער</term> און <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">ליטווינער</term> אין אין [!] <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1091" type="subject">אוניפארמען</term> מיט מאשין-געווער. און מ'האט זיי אלע די <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">קינדער</term> מיט די <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">מוטערס</term> און עלטערע לייט אריינגעשמיסן אין די <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">לאסט-אויטאס</term> – מ'האט זיי <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">געפירט</term> דורך <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html">קאוונע</placeName>.</p>
					<p>נאך די <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">קינדער</term>-<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">אקציע</term> אין אַ מאנאט שפעטער האט מען ליקווידירט דעם <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">לאגער</term>
						<placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">קייליס</placeName>. אַ טייל האט מען געשיקט אויף <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">ריגא</placeName> א טייל אויף <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598286/kazlu-ruda.html">קָאזלאָוואַ רוּדַא</placeName>, 80 מאן
						פאכלייט נאך <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html">קאוונע</placeName>. פארבליבן זיינען אין <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">קייליס</placeName> נור 400 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">מאן</term>. זיי
						זיינען נאך געווען אין <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">קייליס</placeName> 2 וואכן. אין 10 טעג פאר דער <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">באפרייאונג</term> האט מען אלע יידן, צווישן זיי די דאקטוירים <persName ref="#ehri_et_feyglis"
							>פייגלס</persName> און <persName ref="#ehri_et_burak">ד"ר בוראק</persName>, אינזש. <persName ref="#ehri_et_pap">פּאַפּ</persName> (זיי האבן זיך נישט געלאזט נעמען – האט מען זיי בכֹח אריינגעשלעפט אין די אויטאס) מ'האט זיי אוועקגעפירט אויף <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">פָאנַאר</placeName> און דארטן <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">אויסגעשאסן</term>. אין טאג פון דער <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573"
							type="subject">באפרייאונג</term> ווען די <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">ווילנער</placeName> יידן וואס זיינען געווען אין די <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">מאלינעס</term> זיינען געקומען באנאכט
						אויף <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">פאנארי</placeName> – האבן זיי נאך געפונען די <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">פאטאגראפיעס</term> און פיל <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">יידן ניט באגראבן</term> אין די <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">מלבושים</term> – ווייל <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">זיי</term> האבן
						איילענדיג ניט באווייזן זיי צו <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746" type="subject">באגראבן</term>.</p>
					<p>אונטערשריפט: <persName ref="#ehri_et_strazshi_yoffe_sonya">סוניע סטראזשי-יאפפע</persName>.</p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<pb facs="EHRI-ET-YV3540377_01.jpg" n="1"/>
					<p>Testimony</p>
					<p>Given by <persName ref="#ehri_et_strazshi_yoffe_sonya">Sonya Yofe</persName> born in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilna</placeName>, <date when="1946-09-17">17.IX.1946</date>.</p>
					<p>Recorded by <persName ref="#ehri_et_levental_nachman">Levental Nachman</persName></p>
					<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> of <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName> was as follows: two blocks on <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Rydz-Śmigły</placeName> Street,
						where Jewish hat-makers lived and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term>. There were around 2000 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> there, who <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">worked</term> at fur-hat making. The entire time it was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831" type="subject">relatively good</term>. The last period, in <date
							when="1944-06">June 1944</date>, they took fifty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, strong <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term>, to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">Ponar</placeName> to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-943" type="subject">work</term> and they never came back. On <date when="1944-03-27">March 27, 1944</date>, they gathered together the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, young and old <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
							type="subject">dressed</term> them neatly and took them to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-282" type="subject">hospital</term>, ostensibly for an inspection – they took them through one door and out through another. There stood ready
							<term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_ukrainians">Ukrainians</term> and <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_lithuanians">Lithuanians</term> in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1091" type="subject">uniforms</term> with machine guns. And they took all
						the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> with the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822" type="subject">mothers</term> and the old people, flinging them into the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">trucks</term> – they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-521" type="subject">transported</term> them through <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html"
							>Kovno</placeName>.</p>
					<p>After the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">Children’s</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-550" type="subject">Action</term> [Kinder Aktion], a month later, they liquidated the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> of <placeName
							ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName>. Some they sent to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/456172/riga.html">Riga</placeName>, and some to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598286/kazlu-ruda.html">Kazlova-Ruda</placeName> [<placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/598286/kazlu-ruda.html">Kazlų Rūda</placeName>], eighty <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> with a profession to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/598316/kaunas.html"
							>Kovno</placeName>. Only 400 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> remained in <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName>. They were only in <placeName ref="#ehri_et_kailis">Kailis</placeName> for another
						two weeks. Ten days before the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term>, they took all the Jews, among them doctors <persName ref="#ehri_et_feyglis">Feyglis</persName> and Dr. <persName ref="#ehri_et_burak"
							>Burak</persName>, Eng. <persName ref="#ehri_et_pap">Pap</persName> (they did not let themselves be taken – they were dragged out to the trucks with force). They took them to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">Ponar</placeName> and <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532" type="subject">shot</term> them there. On the day of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-573" type="subject">liberation</term>, when the Jews of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/593116/vilnius.html">Vilna</placeName> who were in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hiding places</term> came to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/506699/ponar.html">Ponar</placeName> at
						night, they found the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photographs</term> and many <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">Jews lying unburied</term> in their <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">clothes</term> – because they [the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>] were hurrying and did not manage to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-746"
							type="subject">bury</term> them.</p>
					<p>Signed: <persName ref="#ehri_et_strazshi_yoffe_sonya">Sonya Strazshi-Yoffe</persName></p>
				</div>
